objectives.en:
This course aims:
*	to give an overview of studies that explore cultural heritage in a broad socio-cultural and economic context;
*	to introduce students to the analytical study of cultural policy and cultural processes, as well as to contemporary methods in this field;
*	to analyse the potential and problems related to cultural heritage.

learning_outcomes.en:
Upon successful completion of this course, students should:
*	be familiar with the main theories of cultural heritage and know how to use and combine them; 
*	have gained an overview of opportunities and problems related to political, economic and societal applications of cultural heritage;
*	be capable of linking contemporary cultural processes with the workings of cultural policies;
*	know how to put knowledge obtained in the course into practice in individual and team work.
